        "description": "<p></p><h3 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>What's an Actor?</span></h3><h3 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Actors deliver performances (roles) in live and recorded or filmed settings. An actor may perform live in theatre, opera or variety shows. &nbsp;Pre-recorded performances are required in film, radio, television, ads or material distributed online.</span></h3><h5><span style='font-weight:normal;' id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-4248-a3d8-3996-927c25e91f61'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>Actors present ideas and portray characters in theater, film, television, and other performing arts media. They follow a script to entertain an audience.</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;'>Simply put, an actor portrays a character in a movie, play, television show, theatre or any other mode of performance.</span></p><div><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;'><br></span></div></span><br></h5><p></p> ",
        "duties_&_responsibilities": "<span id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-424a-4def-e005-6eb67f93d53d'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;'>What does an “Actor” Do? &nbsp;Or Duties and Responsibilities</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>Actors typically do the following:</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>·</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>Read scripts and meet with agents and other professionals before accepting a role</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>·</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>Audition in front of directors, producers, and casting directors</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>·</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>Research their character’s personal traits and circumstances to portray the characters authentically</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>·</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>Memorize their lines</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>·</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>Rehearse their lines and performance, including on stage or in front of the camera, with other actors</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>·</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>Discuss their role with the director, producer, and other actors to improve the overall performance of the show</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>·</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>Perform the role, following the director’s directions</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'> </span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>Actors may perform the following tasks:</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;'>Actors audition for various roles. On selection they essay those roles to bring the characters to life. They might work on any level of the profession, from being a junior artiste &nbsp;to a star.</span></p><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;'>Acting involves a lot of rehearsing, working with directors and producers, meeting agents or casting directors, reading scripts, attending meetings, makeup and costumes. Long hours on sets, tours to many different cities, or even countries may be undertaken. Many actors will perform scores of characters during their careers.</span></span>",
        "where_do_they_work": "<span id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-424a-4def-e005-6eb67f93d53d'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-424b-7bf1-6fff-099974148e88'><span style='font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);'>They work in various settings including production studios, theaters, theme parks, or on location (even foreign ones)</span></span><br></p></span>",
        "skills": "<span id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-424a-4def-e005-6eb67f93d53d'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-424c-5fbc-5fb2-0602683b304d'></span></p><ul style='margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.2163636363636363;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Determination and self-confidence</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.2163636363636363;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Good memory</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.2163636363636363;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Ability to cope with changing situations.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.2163636363636363;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Creativity and Emoting skills</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.2163636363636363;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Persistence and Physical stamina. </span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Judging audience taste and reactions.</span></li></ul></span>",
        "important_knowledge_areas": "<span id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-424a-4def-e005-6eb67f93d53d'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-424c-5fbc-5fb2-0602683b304d'></span></p><ul style='margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.2163636363636363;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-424d-53bb-dc8a-6d6fcb9c5e4a'><span style='font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;'>Fine arts, Language skills, Psychology, Communications and media, Sociology and anthropology</span></span><br></p></li></ul></span>",
        "how_to_become_one": "<span id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-424a-4def-e005-6eb67f93d53d'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-424c-5fbc-5fb2-0602683b304d'></span></p><ul style='margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Step 1</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Step 2Minimum Eligibility: </span><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>XII for Private institutes &amp; Graduation in any discipline for Government Institution</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>National/State Level Entrance Exam: </span><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Written test for Government Degree Course.</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Under Graduate Degree/Diploma: </span><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Only available in private institutions</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Post Graduation in</span><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>: Two year Post Graduate Diploma in Acting @FTII</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:3pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>It is believed that actors are born, not made. But formal / informal training can always make a difference.</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Many who specialize in theatre have bachelor’s degrees but that is not a must. You can join a movie group as a junior artiste and take it from there. The sky's the limit.</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.2163636363636363;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span id='docs-internal-guid-91a7008f-424e-617b-c5ad-51922b2f1e2f'></span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt;'><span style='font-size:12pt;font-family:Calibri;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Most actors receive formal preparation through a theatre company or a university drama or theatrical arts program. Classes in drama or filmmaking can prepare for a career as an actor. Dance or music training are an added asset.</span></p></li></ul></span>",
